cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with symbolic model checking algorithm for temporal logic.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper deals with higher-order context-free processes which are a type of process algebra.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with regular sets of configurations and their predecessors.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper deals with data structures that can be seen as a nested stack of stacks.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with symbolic analysis which is a technique used in some machine learning algorithms.
